The article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump and various individuals regarding the U.S.-China trade agreement. Steve Schwarzman and Nelson Peltz comment on the deal, expressing its importance and potential for improving the relationship between the two countries. They also mention the significance of keeping tariffs in place while reaching the agreement. Michael Pillsbury highlights how the President recognized the contributions of individuals and companies involved in the agreement. Pillsbury also mentions that the Chinese view the agreement as globally important for prosperity and peace. Overall, the remarks emphasize the significance of the U.S.-China trade deal.